Haven venus windowed-GL fix for Mesa zink — two hunks, both gated to the
nested-on-Android venus-over-vtest + wl_shm-only-compositor scenario:

 1. src/egl/drivers/dri2/platform_wayland.c — route zink+venus present onto the
    kopper Vulkan-WSI-sw path over a wl_shm-only (pixman) compositor that
    advertises no wl_drm/linux-dmabuf. Without it EGL falls back to drisw and
    nothing is presented (stale/blank window).

 2. src/gallium/drivers/zink/zink_context.c — re-issue the per-frame default UBO
    through the command stream (vkCmdUpdateBuffer) because venus host-visible
    memory isn't reliably GPU-visible over vtest, so the per-frame transform is
    intermittently stale and the model is drawn off-screen (a ~2/3-of-frames
    flicker). Venus-gated.

Device-verified on a Pixel 8 Pro (Mali-G715), guest Ubuntu 24.04 Mesa 25.2.8,
venus over virglrenderer vtest, wl_shm sw-WSI present: glmark2 build/shading/
texture scenes present at 0% flat (240/240 geometry frames) vs ~42% flat with
hunk 2 absent; vkcube (native Vulkan) is unaffected.

