+       * Over some venus transports (notably the vtest socket used without a
+       * kernel virtio-gpu, e.g. nested on Android) a guest-CPU write into
+       * HOST_VISIBLE|HOST_COHERENT memory is intermittently not visible to the
+       * GPU when it later reads the buffer, even though the memory is flagged
+       * coherent.  The default uniform block is uploaded this way every frame
+       * by the state tracker, so the per-frame transform read by the vertex
+       * shader is sometimes stale: the geometry is transformed off-screen and
+       * only the clear colour survives (a ~2/3-of-frames flicker on glmark2).
+       *
+       * Re-issue the just-uploaded constant data through the command stream
+       * (vkCmdUpdateBuffer), which venus delivers reliably, then barrier it for
+       * the shader read.  Venus only; small, 4-byte-aligned UBOs only; never
+       * inside a render pass (vkCmdUpdateBuffer is a transfer command).
